Rivers United recorded their second away victory of the season following a 2-0 win over Adamawa United in the match day 11 of the Nigeria Professional Football League (NPFL) clash at the Pantami Stadium, Gombe on Sunday. Goals from Junior Osaghae and Malachi Ohawume ensured that the Coach Stanley Eguma tutored side got a clean sheet and three points. Also, Emmanuel Ugwuka, Guy Keumian and Bello Lukman were on target as Abia Warriors thrashed league leaders, Plateau United 3-0 at the Umuahia Township Stadium. This is the first time Plateau United conceded three goals in the NPFL since January 2019 when they lost by the same margin to Heartland FC in Owerri while Abia Warriors are undefeated in their last 10 home games since a 0-1 defeat to Nasarawa Utd in March. At the Muhammadu Dikko Stadium, Katsina United survived Jigawa Golden Starsâ€™ scare to secure a 3-2 at home, while Warri Wolves thrashed Kwara United 2-1 at the Warri Township Stadium. Akarandut Orok 51th minute goal was all Akwa United needed to seal a win over Lobi Stars at the Next of Champions Stadium in Uyo while Samuel Kalu 21st minute goal powered FC Ifeanyiubah to victory over Heartland FC. Ten-man Dakkada FC were held to a 1-1 draw by Sunshine Stars in Akure. 